Description: 	
The X-Bolt Eclipse Hunter features a beautiful laminated stock that offers extra stability, a Monte Carlo cheekpiece for improved eye-to-scope alignment and a thumbhole grip for more consistent finger-to-trigger reach. These few changes result in elevated accuracy potential both in the field and from the bench, without adding significant weight.


• Beautiful wood Laminate stock  with thumbhole grip provides durability and a solid, rigid platform for the glass bedded action and stock.
• Monte Carlo cheek piece improves eye-to-scope alignment.
• Durable low-luster blued finish reduces reflective glare
• Button-rifled barrel is triple checked for quality and individually hand chambered and air gauged to ensure consistency and accuracy.
• The target Crown enables the uniform release of gas as the bullet exits the barrel, preventing a shift in trajectory. The Crown is recessed to protect it from accidental damage that degrades accuracy.
• Free floated barrel eliminates contact interference from the fore-end, enabling the superior barrel craftsmanship to perform consistently and accurately.
• Drilled and tapped for X-Lock scope mounts that use four screws for each base to provide a rock solid optic platform.
• Adjustable Feather Trigger minimizes the "human factor" by eliminating creep and take-up — providing a crisp trigger pull that "breaks like glass."
• Low profile action allows you to mount the scope extremely close to the center of the bore to minimize the offset between point of aim and Point of Impact.
• 60° bolt lift keeps the thumb and fingers clear of the scope when cycling the action and allows the bolt to be operated in a smoother/quicker motion.
• Top-tang safety offers easy accessibility without removing your firing hand from the stock. The shooter can quickly manipulate the safety, or verify the position of the safety, without losing your sight picture or cheek weld.
• Detachable Rotary magazine is built from tough polymer and is designed to stop forward movement of the cartridge by contacting the shoulder of the case rather than the tip of the projectile. This prevents bullet tip deformation and recoil induced bullet seating depth change.
• Bolt Unlock Button allows the bolt to be cycled with the safety engaged.
• Innovative Inflex Technology recoil pad uses directional deflection to pull the stock down and away from the face to reduce perceived recoil.

title: For Sale:  FN, FNS9
postcontent:
I need some money for another project, so this gun is on the chopping block.  It's a nearly new FN FNS9.  This pistol already has night sights on it from the factory, making it a perfect candidate for your CCW gun.  

The FNS, in case you dont know, is FN's version of a striker fired pistol.  It's not like the FNX or FNP from their past models with an external hammer and a heavy DA first trigger pull then a lighter SA trigger pull thereafter.  The trigger system on this pistol is more like a Glock or an M&P where every trigger pull is the same weight every time.  

This is the more desirable model with NO external safety lever.  The gun will come in the factory case with three 17rd magazines.  This pistol has been fired 100 times and has been flawless with each trigger pull.  I qualified with it to carry off duty and trust my life and my families life to it.  

With the pistol I'll also include two additional 17rd magazines in the factory box (each loaded and used one time) as well as a quality kydex holster meant for 1.5" belts.  The holster is an approximately $70 value and the spare mags are $35ea if you were to purchase them on your own.  

I'd like to see $625 from the package.  I am located in Burleson, south of Ft. Worth.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Epiphone Les Paul Electric Guitar, Amp and effects
location: Holly Springs, North West Mississippi, Mississippi
postcontent:
For sale or trade, Epiphone Less Paul Plus Top Pro electric guitar, Marshall amp and Johnson J station. This is everything you need to play guitar by yourself or up to small gigs. The guitar was bought last November and I just don;t have time to play it. I've had the amp and J-Station for a while, but they both have very little use. Everything works and sounds great. I will sell all of it together for $550. I've got close to $1000 in all this so please no lowball offer's. I am located near Holly Springs, MS and I get to Olive Branch, MS? Memphis, TN regularly.

The Guitar is a 6 string Epiphone Les Paul Plus Top Pro in transparent black with chrome pickup covers, they look gold in the picture but that is just the lighting. It features ProBucker pickups that offer the classic Les Paul sound, as well as dual coil tapping so that you can set the sound of classic no humbucker electric guitars as well as that deep Les Paul Sound. Just pull up or push down in the volume controls to switch between humbucker and single coil pickups. The guitar also comes with a Epiphone hard case. The guitar is in excellent condition with very little play time on it, maybe 3 or 4 hours total. The guitar and case would cast about $590 plus tax new. I will sell them for $410.

The amp is a Marshall CD15. They don;t make these anymore. It has the classic Marshall sound with an overdrive channel. It is loud enough for small gigs. It also has Headphone output and an imput jack that lets you plug your CD player, MP3 player, Ipod or Iphone into it so that you can play along with your favorite bands. This amp shows signs of being moved around a lot, but has very little play time on it. I bought it right before I got out of playing Guitar about 10 years ago. It's just sat in the corner since. $75.

Lastly is a Johnson J-Station. This is a amp modeling effects processor. You can get just about any sound you want out of this. It has factory preset Amp effects set ups, you can also set up lots of custom effects and amp combos and store them on the J-station. With the addition of a few cables you can plug this into you computer and record what you are playing. They don't make these anymore and they are pretty sought after. As you can see in the pick there are a few chips in the paint, but everything works great. I've seen these for $250 on ebay. I will sell it for $110.

As far as trades go I'm mainly looking for guns. A Glock 19 or 26 is number one on my list. I'd also be interested in Savage bolt action .22 and .17 HMR rifles, a 12 gauge shotgun, 10/22, heavy barreled .22s, 1911s, Ruger MK II, MK III and 22/45 pistols, AR-15 varmint upper halves, Mini-14s and varmint or tactical rifles in .223 or a complete reloading set up.

postcontent:
Update: 6/22/14:  The listing, "Schmidt & Bender Scope 5-25x56 PMII LP/MTC/LT H2CMR CCW" in Michigan is a scam.  The con artist uses the email "dagibson1967@gmail.com".  He uses the phone number, "1-518-635-3215", a New York number.  "David Gibson" is not a native English speaker and is using a recycled ad and picture from the very first one he posted in Texas in early May 2014. He wants you to send a check to, "Magaret Gibson, 270 Orange Street, Albany, NY 12210". The home at that address looks like a crack house. Go to google maps.com and see for yourself.  He stole the rifle scope pictures from a July 2013 www.snipershide.com listing.  He also cut and pasted the exact wording from the original posting. Flag him and shut him down.

Also, if you live in the area, file a local police report and request that they subpoena his MAC IP address from the computer server provider, which will give his physical location of where he is e-mailing from, which will lead to his identity and true place of residence. You can do the same with his phone number and subpoena the phone company as they can determine his location as well.
